shocks to help treat paralytic strokes and hysteria, and even suggested applying shocks to the head to treat depressive disorders. He also strove to topple one of the greatest fads in eighteenth-century medicine: mesmerism.Doctor Franklin's Medicine looks at these and the many other contributions that Franklin made to the progress of medical knowledge, including a look at how Franklin approached his own chronic illnesses of painful gout and a large bladder stone. Written in accessible prose and filled with new information on the breadth of Franklin's interests and activities, Doctor Franklin's Medicine reveals the impressive medical legacy of this Founding Father.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aFamous PersonsvBiographyzUnited States. 0aHISTORYzUnited StatesvColonial Period (1600-1775). 0aHistory of MedicinevBiographyzUnited States. 0aHistory, 18th CenturyvBiographyzUnited States. 0aMedicinezUnited StatesxHistoryx18th century. 0aMedicinezUnited StatesxHistoryy18th century. 0aScientistszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aScientistszUnited StatesxHistoryx18th century. 0aScientistszUnited StatesxHistoryy18th century. 4aHistory of Science. 7aHISTORY / United States / Colonial Period (1600-1775).2bisacsh  aAmerican History.  aAmerican Studies.  aGeneral.  aHistory of Science.  aNatural History.  aScience.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn Press eBook Package American Historyz978311041349608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn Press eBook Package Complete Collectionz978311041345808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Pennsylvania Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311045954840uhttps://doi.org/10.9783/978081220191840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780812201918423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/